    "Kim et al. (2013) focus on addressing the bleed-through issue in multi-color fluorescence microscopy.",
    "This issue, akin to the challenge of distinguishing specific features in fluorescent minerals or fossils, involves the misidentification of fluorescent probe species, leading to false colocalization and correlation in imaging.",
    "The authors present a statistical approach that accurately identifies and corrects bleed-through between fluorescent channels.",
    "It utilizes an algorithm that analyzes the spatial distribution of fluorescence intensities across multiple channels.",
    "This correction is crucial for reliable interpretation and analysis, similar to the challenges faced in fluorescence microscopy."
